1. AWS EC2 SETUP (UBUNTU)
EC2 Creation (AWS Console)

Launch EC2

Choose Ubuntu AMI

Instance type: t2.micro

Create / use key pair

Security Group:

Port 22 (SSH)

Port 5000 (Flask)

Launch instance

üîπ 2. CONNECT TO EC2 (SSH)
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

üîπ 3. SYSTEM UPDATE (LINUX COMMANDS)
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

üîπ 4. INSTALL REQUIRED PACKAGES (VERY IMPORTANT)
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv python3-full mysql-server -y


Check versions:

python3 --version
pip3 --version

üîπ 5. CREATE PYTHON VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate


(You saw: (venv) in terminal)

üîπ 6. INSTALL PYTHON LIBRARIES (INSIDE VENV)
pip install flask mysql-connector-python


üëâ You faced externally-managed-environment error
üëâ Fixed correctly by using virtual environment ‚úÖ

üîπ 7. MYSQL LOGIN (ROOT ‚Äì UBUNTU SOCKET AUTH)
sudo mysql

üîπ 8. MYSQL DATABASE COMMANDS (ALL USED)
SHOW DATABASES;
CREATE DATABASE employee_db;
USE employee_db;

üîπ 9. CREATE TABLES (SQL)
Employees Table
CREATE TABLE employees (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  emp_code VARCHAR(30),
  name VARCHAR(100),
  department VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(100),
  salary INT,
  status VARCHAR(20)
);

Users Table
CREATE TABLE users (
  username VARCHAR(50) PRIMARY KEY,
  password VARCHAR(100),
  role VARCHAR(20)
);

üîπ 10. INSERT USERS (LOGIN DATA)
INSERT INTO users VALUES
('admin','admin123','ADMIN'),
('hr','hr123','HR'),
('viewer','view123','VIEWER');

üîπ 11. SHOW & VERIFY TABLES
SHOW TABLES;
SELECT * FROM users;

üîπ 12. MYSQL ROOT ACCESS ERROR (IMPORTANT ISSUE)

‚ùå Error:

Access denied for user 'root'@'localhost'


‚úÖ Correct Fix Used (BEST PRACTICE)

üîπ 13. CREATE MYSQL APPLICATION USER
CREATE USER 'empuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'emp@123';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON employee_db.* TO 'empuser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


Exit MySQL:

exit;

üîπ 14. TEST MYSQL CONNECTION USING PYTHON
db_test.py
import mysql.connector

db = mysql.connector.connect(
    host="localhost",
    user="empuser",
    password="emp@123",
    database="employee_db"
)

print("MySQL Connected Successfully")


Run:

python db_test.py

üîπ 15. CREATE FLASK APPLICATION FILE
nano app.py


(You added full Flask code with)

Login

Dashboard

Add employee

Update status

Role-based access

üîπ 16. CREATE FRONTEND FILES
mkdir templates
nano templates/login.html
nano templates/dashboard.html

üîπ 17. RUN FLASK APPLICATION
python app.py


Flask running on:

http://0.0.0.0:5000

üîπ 18. OPEN APPLICATION IN BROWSER
http://3.6.160.242:5000


‚úî Login page opened
‚úî Dashboard opened

